 Russia says 'Barbie' and 'Oppenheimer' films don't live up to country's values https://www.nme.com/news/film/barbie-and-oppenheimer-films-russia-values-3492147?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=barbie-and-oppenheimer-films-russia-valuesCharlotte Krol Fri, 01 Sep 2023 11:32:46 +0000 Film NewsNews https://www.nme.com/?p=3492147 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/barbie-oppenheimer@2000x1270.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="&#039;Barbie&#039; and &#039;Oppenheimer&#039;" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/barbie-oppenheimer@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/barbie-oppenheimer@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/barbie-oppenheimer@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/barbie-oppenheimer@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/barbie-oppenheimer@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/barbie-oppenheimer@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> Deputy Culture Minister Andrei Malyshev has rejected an appeal to screen the blockbusters</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/barbie-and-oppenheimer-films-russia-values-3492147">Russia says &#39;Barbie&#39; and &#39;Oppenheimer&#39; films don&#39;t live up to country&#39;s values</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/barbie-oppenheimer@2000x1270.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="&#039;Barbie&#039; and &#039;Oppenheimer&#039;" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/barbie-oppenheimer@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/barbie-oppenheimer@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/barbie-oppenheimer@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/barbie-oppenheimer@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/barbie-oppenheimer@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/barbie-oppenheimer@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/films/barbie"><em>Barbie</em></a> and <a href="https://www.nme.com/films/oppenheimer"><em>Oppenheimer</em></a> don&#39;t live up to Russia&#39;s values and shouldn&#39;t be screened in the country, its Deputy Culture Minister has said.</p><ul class="post-content-read-more"><li> <strong>READ MORE:<a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/film-reviews/barbie-review-margot-robbie-ryan-gosling-3470019"><em>Barbie</em> review: Greta Gerwig&#39;s grown-up toy story is fantastic fun</a></strong></li></ul><p> Andrei Malyshev rejected a request by vice-speaker of Russia&#39;s parliament, Vladislav Davankov, who&#39;d written to officials asking them to launch a pilot scheme where cinemas could show popular new releases.</p><p> The TASS news agency [via <a href="https://www.politico.eu/article/barbie-oppenheimer-cinema-values-russia/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Politico</em></a> ] reported yesterday (August 31) that Malyshev rejected the appeal based on his preferences for movies and which content he believes the Russian people value. The West has boycotted Russia since it launched its invasion of Ukraine in February 2022, meaning that new Western films are not currently shown in the country.</p><p> Davankov had lobbied the Russian government to allow bootleg screenings despite the Hollywood embargo.</p><p> Malyshev wrote: “We believe that the films you have proposed for viewing by the citizens of our country – <em>Barbie</em> and <em>Oppenheimer</em> – do not meet the aims and objectives set out by the head of state, to preserve and strengthen traditional Russian spiritual and moral values.” </p><figure id="attachment_3473745" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3473745" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3473745" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Barbie_Gosling_Robbie_Dreamhouse.jpg" alt="芭比" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Barbie_Gosling_Robbie_Dreamhouse.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Barbie_Gosling_Robbie_Dreamhouse-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Barbie_Gosling_Robbie_Dreamhouse-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Barbie_Gosling_Robbie_Dreamhouse-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Barbie_Gosling_Robbie_Dreamhouse-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Barbie_Gosling_Robbie_Dreamhouse-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3473745" class="wp-caption-text"> Margot Robbie and Ryan Gosling during the opening dance scene in &#39;Barbie&#39;. CREDIT: Warner Bros</figcaption></figure><p> Instead, Malyshev believes that Russians get suitable entertainment and information from domestic productions including animated children&#39;s film <em>Cheburashka</em> and <em>The Challenge</em> , a Russian state-backed film shot on the International Space Station.</p><p> According to the minister, making up for the lack of foreign content in the wake of Western firms&#39; exit from the country has stimulated the country&#39;s own industry. <em>Cheburashka</em> , however, has an average rating of 7.2 out of 10 on Russian film website <a href="https://sso.passport.yandex.ru/push?retpath=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kinopoisk.ru%2Ffilm%2F4370148%2F%3Futm_referrer%3Dwww.google.com&amp;uuid=a3414e1e-ff50-4321-9a8f-0c9b30f220e6" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Kinopoisk</em></a> .</p><p> Meanwhile, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/theres-a-woman-called-barbie-oppenheimer-and-shes-been-having-a-difficult-time-3491539">a woman named Barbara “Barbie” Oppenheimer is having a tough time being taken seriously</a> following the box office success of “ <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/barbie-currently-beating-oppenheimer-at-box-office-3471864">Barbenheimer</a> “.</p><p>芭芭拉·奥本海默 (Barbara Oppenheimer) 是一位退休的波士顿大学教授，也是五个孩子的祖母，住在马萨诸塞州牛顿，但今年“巴本海默”热潮的兴奋让她在夏天的事情变得有些复杂。 </p><figure id="attachment_3476542" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3476542" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3476542" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Cillian-Murphy-Oppenheimer-2000x1270-1.jpg" alt="《奥本海默》中的希里安·墨菲" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Cillian-Murphy-Oppenheimer-2000x1270-1.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Cillian-Murphy-Oppenheimer-2000x1270-1-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Cillian-Murphy-Oppenheimer-2000x1270-1-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Cillian-Murphy-Oppenheimer-2000x1270-1-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Cillian-Murphy-Oppenheimer-2000x1270-1-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Cillian-Murphy-Oppenheimer-2000x1270-1-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3476542" class="wp-caption-text"> 《奥本海默》中的希里安·墨菲。图片来源：环球影业</figcaption></figure><p>奥本海默在接受<a href="https://slate.com/culture/2023/08/barbie-oppenheimer-movie-2023-barbara-interview.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Slate</em></a>采访时表示，每当她大声说出自己的名字时，很多人都认为她在开玩笑。</p><p>她回忆起最近假期期间一个特别令人困惑的时刻，她说：“当我在酒店办理入住时，我说，‘芭比·奥本海默！’那家伙说，‘你在开我的玩笑吗？’”</p><p>奥本海默说，她“在[电影]上映的那个周末，世界各地的大学朋友给我发短信，充满了各种污蔑，你知道……‘炸弹和重磅炸弹’。”</p><p> “这很有趣！”她谈到了混乱。 “他们一起推出这些电影是一件很棒的事情。它确实把人们带回了电影院。”</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/barbie-and-oppenheimer-films-russia-values-3492147">Russia says &#39;Barbie&#39; and &#39;Oppenheimer&#39; films don&#39;t live up to country&#39;s values</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
